  "prompt": "When is surge pricing on Uber generally in effect in Sarasota and how high does it go?",
  "response": "Surge pricing on Uber in Sarasota, like in other cities, typically occurs during times of high demand relative to the number of available drivers. This can happen during:\n\n1. **Peak Hours:**  \n   - **Weekday Commutes:** Morning (7-9 AM) and evening (5-7 PM) rush hours.\n   - **Weekend Evenings:** Especially on Friday and Saturday nights, late evenings (10 PM - 2 AM) when people are heading out or returning from events.\n\n2. **Special Events:**  \n   - Concerts, festivals, sports events, or other large gatherings that increase demand for rides.\n\n3. **Weather Conditions:**  \n   - Bad weather, such as rain or storms, can lead to surges as fewer drivers are on the road and more people request rides.\n\n4. **Holidays:**  \n   - Popular travel times, like New Year's Eve, Thanksgiving, or other major holidays.\n\n### How High Does Surge Pricing Go?  \nThe surge multiplier varies based on the level of demand and can range from **1.2x to 3x or higher**. In extreme cases, such as major events or severe weather, it can go even higher (e.g., 5x or more). The exact multiplier is displayed in the Uber app when you request a ride.\n\nTo avoid surprises, it\u2019s a good idea to check the app before booking and consider waiting a few minutes for the surge to subside if possible. Uber also sometimes offers upfront pricing during surges, so you\u2019ll know the exact cost before confirming the ride.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
